HEADWORD: Lock washer
<hw>Lock" wash`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A washer that is
not completely smooth or flat, designed to prevent a nut from loosening,
placed under the nut on a screw or bolt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

